6. Testing Requirements
============================================================

Use GoogleTest.

Implement both unit tests and system tests.

[Unit Tests]
Write tests for:
- Initial controller state
- Start cleaning behavior
- Stop cleaning behavior
- Default forward movement
- Front obstacle avoidance
- Left/right obstacle decision
- Dead-end behavior
- Dust detection and power boost
- Return from power boost to normal cleaning

[System Tests]
Write scenario-based simulator tests for:
- Open area cleaning scenario
- Single obstacle avoidance scenario
- Dead-end escape scenario
- Dust cleaning scenario
- Mixed map scenario containing obstacles and dust

Each system test should check:
- The RVC does not move into obstacles.
- The RVC continues cleaning after avoiding obstacles.
- The RVC boosts cleaning power when dust is detected.
- The RVC eventually returns to normal cleaning power.
- The RVC visits expected states during the scenario.

